# Forms (react-hook-form + zod)

## Canonical stack

Profile page (`src/app/(app)/profile/`) is the reference implementation.

| Layer | Tool |
| ----- | ---- |
| Client forms | `react-hook-form` + `@hookform/resolvers/zod` |
| UI | shadcn `Form`, `FormField`, `Input`, `Textarea` from `@/components/ui/form` |
| Validation | Shared zod schema in route `_lib/` (e.g. `profile-form-schema.ts`) |
| Server boundary | Same schema via `safeParse` in Server Actions — never return raw `ZodError` |
| Success feedback | Per save model below — toast (explicit submit) or inline indicator (blur-save) |
| Errors | `InlineError` (operational) / `ErrorPanel` (fault) per `error-handling.mdc` |

## Save model

Pick the save trigger by form shape. This is the routing rule for any new form:

| Form shape | Save trigger | Success feedback |
| ---------- | ------------ | ---------------- |
| Inline, independent fields (each stands alone) | Save on blur, per field | Inline transient indicator (see `notifications.mdc`) — **not** a toast |
| Modal, coupled fields that submit as a unit, or higher-stakes (e.g. password change) | Explicit submit button | Toast (`showSuccessToast`) |
| File upload | Persist on upload completion — no separate save step | Inline indicator on the control |

- **Blur-save:** validate the field on blur and **never persist an invalid field**; save only changed fields.
- **Why inline, not toast, for blur-save:** a toast per field blur is disproportionate for silent auto-save and stacks when the user tabs between fields. Toasts are reserved for explicit, discrete actions. See `notifications.mdc`.
- **Coupled fields** (e.g. new + confirm password) validate and submit as a unit, never per-field.
- **Higher-stakes mutations** (password, email, anything that can lock a user out) use explicit submit, typically in a modal, and re-authenticate at the server boundary where the provider supports it.

## Password fields & autofill

Any form with credential fields carries the correct `autocomplete` tokens so password
managers and browsers behave correctly. **Applies to every form with credential fields,
including the `useState` auth forms** — it is independent of the form library.

- Account identifier (email) → `autocomplete="username"`.
- Existing password (sign-in; current-password in a change) → `autocomplete="current-password"`.
- New password **and** its confirm field → `autocomplete="new-password"`. This token is what
  triggers the manager's generate-password offer and prevents the old password autofilling
  into the new field.
- Pair password fields with a username field so the manager knows which credential to
  save/update — even in a change-password or post-recovery form where no email is otherwise
  shown, render it referencing the account email (visually hidden is fine, but it must be in
  the DOM).
- Forms must be real `<form>` elements so managers detect them as credential forms.

## Client pattern

```typescript
const form = useForm<ProfileFormValues>({
  resolver: zodResolver(profileFormSchema),
  defaultValues,
})

// Submit via useTransition or local isLoading; call Server Action; branch on envelope
```

Auth forms (`login-form`, `sign-up-form`, etc.) remain `useState` until intentionally migrated — new settings/profile-style forms use this stack.

## Server Action pattern

1. `getUser()` — reject unauthenticated with operational error envelope
2. `parseXInput(input)` — shared zod `safeParse`; map first issue to user-safe message
3. Mutate via Supabase server client (RLS-scoped)
4. `revalidatePath` for affected routes
5. Return `{ success: true, data }` or `{ success: false, error: { message, code, kind } }`

See [`src/app/(app)/profile/actions.ts`](../../src/app/(app)/profile/actions.ts) and [`src/app/admin/users/actions.ts`](../../src/app/admin/users/actions.ts).

